    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>Once cursed bards or shamans, grave-singers are undead conjurers who command the dead through terrible song. Their voice resonates like wind through a tomb — hauntingly beautiful and deeply wrong. They weave dirges that strengthen undead allies and sap the will of the living with weakening elegy. A grave-singer at the heart of an undead formation can turn a skirmish into a rout, raising fallen foes and singing the living into despair.</p>",
